T {DUT} 370 -480 0 0 0.8 0.8 {}
T {External control signals} 100 -870 0 0 0.6 0.6 {}
T {We need a way to differentiate 
calibration, from real action, and 
that's the START signal (START means 
we're doing compares).  That START 
also needs to be inverted to use the 
passthrough and send the output
to the ADJ.} 430 -810 0 0 0.3 0.3 {}
T {Comparator output: 
tells us if PLUS side
is above MINUS input.
The 'delta' is just
"plus - minus", so 
comp should match
behaviour.} 560 -280 0 0 0.3 0.3 {}
T {Inputs} 740 -890 0 0 0.6 0.6 {}
T {Control} 1620 -870 0 0 0.6 0.6 {}
T {Need to calibrate at the start, so I delay
the sine input long enough to play with 
CALIBTHRESH in the stimuli file.  Since
both these V sources (the sin and 
the PWL generated by the stimuli) conflict
on the input, resistors are used to sep 
them out.} -220 -380 0 0 0.3 0.3 {}
T {During calibration (start low) the comparator output charges up the cap in a way that will 
basically cancel out the offset between plus and minus.  The start goes high and that charge 
on ADJ either sources or sinks enough current off of one leg to keep things behaving nicely.  

It stays charged a long time, probably don't need to cal too often.} 1650 -380 0 0 0.3 0.3 {}
T {Am using both a stimuli file
and a number of agauss() params
in sim to
 * do calibration step
 * vary VCC, VTHRESH (MINUS), TEMP and sine INAMPlitude} 290 -100 0 0 0.3 0.3 {}
